 َـٰهُمْ كُلَّ مُمَزَّقٍ ۚ إِنَّ فِى ذَٰل
 ِكَ لَـَٔايَـٰتٍ لِّكُلِّ صَبَّارٍ شَكُ
 ورٍ\n\nEN: But [insolently] they said\, "Our Lord\, lengthen the distan
 ce between our journeys\," and wronged themselves\, so We made them narrat
 ions¹ and dispersed them in total dispersion. Indeed in that are signs fo
 r everyone patient and grateful.\nSV: Men då sade de: "Herre! Förläng a
